Learn the rules of variable naming in Python.

Rules
Make sure your variable names are descriptive
Don't have spaces between words
Don't start with numbers
Don't use special words like print or input
Choose simple words that are less likely to become typos
Check the company style guidelines if you start work at a company
=============================================================================================================================

#Below code prints three Hello world!

print("Hello world!\nHello world!\nHello world!")

O/p-
Hello world!
Hello world!
Hello world!


# This line of code will take an input using the input() function
print("Hello " + input("What is your name?") + "!")

O/p-

What is your name?Ashish
Hello Ashish!


#One line code to take i/p and print len 
print(len(input("What is your name?")))

O/p-
What is your name?Angela Yu
9

#Above line code converted to multiple lines improving readability
username = input("What is your name?")
length = len(username)
print(length)

O/p-
What is your name?Angela
6
